<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="ap_subpoena.article"><B>ap_subpoena.article</B></a>
<DD>1993 article regarding the controversy surrounding
    netwide distribution of PGP, a strong encryption program, much to
    the dismay of the NSA
<DT><a href="eff_pgp_defense.announce"><B>eff_pgp_defense.announce</B></a>
<DD>announcement by the EFF stating that it would
    support Phil Zimmermann's defense dealing with constitutional issues,
    investigate the PGP case and other cryptography cases, and launch a campaign
    that wouldraise money to support these endevors.
<DT><a href="gov_access.article"><B>gov_access.article</B></a>
<DD>An article describing the timeline of a person who
    was called before a grand jury regarding PGP and Zimmermann
<DT><a href="itar_aeca_caaa_implications.debate"><B>itar_aeca_caaa_implications.debate</B></a>
<DD>article discussing the implications
    of the illegality of transporting public records via encryption to
    countries (South Africa) that were inelligible to recieve public record.
<DT><a href="nyt_subpoena.article"><B>nyt_subpoena.article</B></a>
<DD>article printed in September, 1993 by the New York
    Times that discusses the Federal Govt. investigating companies that
    have sold encryption programs
<DT><a href="rickard_pgp_nii.article"><B>rickard_pgp_nii.article</B></a>
<DD>Article from Boardwatch Magazine describing the
    social ramifications of PGP and encryption on the internet.
<DT><a href="sussman.article"><B>sussman.article</B></a>
<DD>article about Phil Zimmermann and his creation of the
    stong encryption program PGP, that has the Feds in an uproar.
<DT><a href="usatty_pgp_011196.announce"><B>usatty_pgp_011196.announce</B></a>
<DD>short and unrevealing press release from the 
    U.S. Attorney for No. Calif. announcing that the govt. is ceasing it's 
    investigation of PGP author Phil Zimmermann, declining to prosecute 
    anyone in connection with the case, and closing the case.
</DL>

