                                  MAILER.HTML
                                       
   This is the html document that lets the user initialize the interface.
   It needs to be somewhere in your WWW server's publicly-available
   directories and needs to have the ACTION= line edited to point to the
   "first" script.
   
   
     _________________________________________________________________
   

<title>Remailer Interface Initializer</title>

<h1>Initialize the interface</h1>

<FORM METHOD="POST" ACTION="/cgi-bin/init-mailer.pl">

<input type="submit" name="submit" value="Initialize">

</FORM><P>

This will finger <<i>ghio@andrew.cmu.edu</i>> and retrieve a list
of current remailers.  It uses this information to build the
remailer menu, so the list of remailers you see is as current
as possible.<P>

Brought to you by
<a href="http://www.vis.colostate.edu/docs/cvl/staff/nate/whoami.html">
Nate Sammons <<i>nate@vis.colostate.edu</i>></a>

