<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="va_sb1067_95.act"><B>va_sb1067_95.act</B></a>
<DD>Senate bill 1067, singed into law May 1995, like clone 
    legislation in Montana, Kansas and elsewhere expands definition of 
    &quot;child pornography&quot; to cover obscene faked child porn (pointless - 
    it's already illegal) and non-obscene art that does not feature real 
    children at all (unconstitutional - such art is protected under the 
    First Amendment).
</DL>

